---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Projects"
  description="Portfolio of AI systems, operations tooling, workflow automation, and implementation case studies."
>
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Projects</h1>
    <p class="page-intro">Systems, tools, and delivery work that show how I approach AI implementation and operations.</p>

    <div class="projects-grid">

      <div class="project-card">
        <div class="card-header">
          <h3><a href="/jules/">Jules AI Collaborator</a></h3>
          <span class="status status-live">Live</span>
        </div>
        <p>
          Open-source AI operational system that runs my business. Content pipelines, research, scheduling, reporting, coding, and operational context in one workflow.
        </p>
        <div class="tech-tags">
          <span>Claude Code</span><span>Python</span><span>Bash</span><span>MCP</span>
        </div>
        <div class="card-links">
          <a href="/jules/">How it works &rarr;</a>
          <a href="https://github.com/jonathanmalkin/jules">GitHub &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="project-card">
        <div class="card-header">
          <h3><a href="/articles/hormozi-brain-agent/">Hormozi Brain Claude Project</a></h3>
          <span class="status status-live">Live</span>
        </div>
        <p>
          Public starter kit for building an Alex Hormozi-style Claude Project from public material. Fast path instructions, distilled knowledge files, eval prompts, and a source manifest for upgrading to a full build.
        </p>
        <div class="tech-tags">
          <span>Claude Projects</span><span>Prompt Design</span><span>Knowledge Packaging</span><span>GitHub</span>
        </div>
        <div class="card-links">
          <a href="/articles/hormozi-brain-agent/">Article &rarr;</a>
          <a href="https://github.com/jonathanmalkin/hormozi-brain-claude-project">GitHub &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="project-card">
        <div class="card-header">
          <h3>Discord Server Manager</h3>
          <span class="status status-archived">Archived</span>
        </div>
        <p>
          Operations suite for a high-volume Discord community. Automated onboarding, role assignment, moderation tracking, health reporting, engagement analytics, dead-channel detection, and permissions auditing.
        </p>
        <div class="tech-tags">
          <span>Python</span><span>TypeScript</span><span>discord.py</span><span>SQLite</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="project-card">
        <div class="card-header">
          <h3><a href="https://github.com/jonathanmalkin/builtwithjon">Marketing Infrastructure</a></h3>
          <span class="status status-live">Live</span>
        </div>
        <p>
          builtwithjon.com and supporting properties. Lean Astro delivery, Cloudflare deploys, structured metadata, sitemap/RSS/llms.txt support, and the operational plumbing behind a small AI business.
        </p>
        <div class="tech-tags">
          <span>Astro</span><span>Cloudflare Workers</span><span>CSS</span>
        </div>
        <div class="card-links">
          <a href="https://github.com/jonathanmalkin/builtwithjon">GitHub &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="project-card card-wide">
        <div class="card-header">
          <h3>Utilities</h3>
          <span class="status status-mixed">Mixed</span>
        </div>
        <div class="utility-grid">
          <div class="utility-item">
            <strong>Whisper Repetition Fix</strong>
            <p>Homebrew wrapper intercepting whisper-cli with anti-repetition flags. Companion post-processor: 90+ hallucination filters, n-gram dedup, Claude Haiku fallback.</p>
            <div class="tech-tags">
              <span>Python</span><span>Homebrew</span><span>Claude API</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="utility-item">
            <strong>Event Distribution</strong>
            <p>AI-assisted event creation and multi-platform distribution with creative generation, scheduling, and RSVP operations baked into one workflow.</p>
            <div class="tech-tags">
              <span>TypeScript</span><span>OpenAI</span><span>REST APIs</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="utility-item">
            <strong>Plane Sync</strong>
            <p>Bidirectional markdown-to-Plane.so sync with cursor pagination, state reconciliation, and 1Password credentials.</p>
            <div class="tech-tags">
              <span>TypeScript</span><span>Plane API</span><span>1Password</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
